::Q1::Which Playwright API is used to intercept network requests? {=page.route ~page.mock ~route.intercept}
::Q2::Which route mode completely drops the request? {=abort ~fulfill ~continue}
::Q3::Which option is used to return synthetic responses? {=fulfill ~abort ~fetch}
::Q4::Which API allows modifying request headers before forwarding? {=route.continue ~route.fulfill ~route.abort}
::Q5::Which URL pattern type supports regex? {=RegExp pattern ~glob pattern ~predicate only}
::Q6::Which response property automatically sets Content-Type to JSON? {=json ~body ~path}
::Q7::Which method proxies and modifies a real response? {=route.fetch + fulfill ~route.real ~route.proxy}
::Q8::Which route scope affects all pages in a context? {=context.route ~page.route ~browser.route}
::Q9::Which fulfill option serves a response from file? {=path ~file ~serve}
::Q10::Which method simulates a network timeout error? {=route.abort('timedout') ~route.fulfill({timeout:true}) ~route.delay()}
::Q11::What determines handler execution priority? {=Registration order ~Alphabetical order ~Pattern length}
::Q12::Which method passes control to next matching handler? {=route.fallback ~route.continue ~route.pass}
::Q13::Which feature records real network activity for replay? {=HAR file ~Proxy cache ~Mock cache}
::Q14::Which handler simulates retry scenario? {=Stateful mock ~Static fulfill ~HAR replay}
::Q15::Which route option limits mocks to N invocations? {=times ~limit ~repeat}
::Q16::Which mock type stores CRUD state in memory? {=Fake backend class ~Static JSON mocks ~HAR mocks}
::Q17::Which command records HAR from CLI? {=playwright open --save-har=... ~playwright record-har ~playwright capture}
::Q18::Which abort reason simulates DNS failure? {=namenotresolved ~internetdisconnected ~failed}
::Q19::Which mocking mode is best for full offline regression? {=HAR replay ~route.abort ~fake backend}
::Q20::Which method removes all route handlers on a page? {=page.unrouteAll ~page.clearRoutes ~page.reset}